[Name] GThumb
[Summary] GTK+ image viewer and browser
[Description] GThumb is a image viewer and browser for the GNOME
desktop. The viewer supports BMP, JPEG (with EXIF data), GIF
(including animations), PNG, TIFF, ICO and XPM. The browser use
thumbnailing, which shares database with Nautilus, and bookmarking to
make the browsing easy. You can add comments to your images, organize
them in catalogs and even do simple editing such as resizing and red
eye removal.
GThumb can also import images from digital cameras using libGPhoto2
and create web albums, slide shows and index images.
